      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even with proper placement and reinforcement, rebar that's not placed correctly can lead to issues. Inadequate rebar can cause premature cracking, reduced tensile strength, or even failure, depending on the severity of the mistake. Visible signs of a problem may include gapping between the rebar and the concrete (lassoing) or a weakened bond at the rebar-concrete interface, which can lead to a sudden failure if the loads increase. Regular inspections and monitoring of structures can help identify potential issues, but in many cases, rebar failures can be catastrophic and even catastrophic.",
      "source": "target",
